<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-495-784  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 495 784.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  May 21 1990 v4 n20 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Drug bill would ease Fed access to records. (the National DrugControl Strategy Implementation Act of 1990)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob; Richardson, Jennifer.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A new bill is before Congress.andP;  The National Drug Control StrategyImplementation Act of 1990 would permit law-enforcement agenciesto obtain a search warrant, instead of a wiretap order, to gainaccess to stored electronic and voice mail, cable TV systemrecords and personal financial information.andP;  The Office ofNational Drug Control Policy views these communications asanalogous to a letter.andP;  But civil liberties groups say the bill isan intrusion on privacy rights.andP;  A provision of the bill permitsgrand juries to subpoena records of cable television companies.andO;The bill also would permit local, state, federal and internationallaw-enforcement agencies to supply information on suspected drugdealers to the Treasury Department's Financial Crimes EnforcementNetwork without notifying the individual about the transfer ofsuch information.andP;  The American Bankers Association tentativelyendorses the bill.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     LegislationPrivacyNational GovernmentBankingInformation Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>